##Drifting down the highway

Wechat, renwumag1980

Feature Introduction, the best Chinese character report

Where people come from during outbreaks is very important. Xiao Hongbing, 50, said he was from a "non-epidemic area, " referring to his own light van. Resident 1, health.

Not only was the van a "no-plague zone, " it was also a temporary "home. ". He is probably a obedient citizen to the praise of public health experts. He does not leave his home for several days and nights. He mainly eats instant noodles for a living and keeps to himself.

In front of the "home" is the striking Hubei M3B350, which is why he can not leave the "home" . He left Tianmen, Hubei Province, on Jan. 7 to make a delivery to the provinces. But from the first day of the New Year to the fifth day of the New Year, because of a character for "e" , he was like a small boat floating in the sea. He could not find a place to dock. At every port, the people on the shore would push him back to the center of the sea, he was isolated in the sea, drifting alone, rough seas, he did not dare to rest.

He drifted on the highway for four days and nights. People always tell him, "go home to your family, " which means his real family, in Tianmen, Hubei Province. No one cares how he can get back to Tianmen. Due to the information isolation, Xiao Hongbing also does not know when the highways in Hubei were shut down in the end. What is the development trajectory of the epidemic in Wuhan and Hubei in the end, nor did he know if there were any hotels in his foreign land for the people of Hubei Province -- if there were, he would not want to stay there. He just knew from the ostracism toward him and his "e" Van that the gate was becoming indecisive, an unreachable destination in the navigation of his mobile phone.

A Weibo post by Xiao Hongbing, who cried "I'm too tired" after being taken in at a service area on Hanzhong's North Expressway, attracted public attention yesterday. In fact, the service area had arranged a hotel room for him yesterday, similar to the standard room, and he was finally able to spread his legs and sleep in bed. Returning home became a less urgent matter for a while, and he was even more worried about how he would support his true home, the Foshan -- an unemployed wife -- in a future where the epidemic seemed unlikely to end soon, vulnerable parents and a son about to enter junior high school.

Here's what Xiao Hongbing says:

By Jing Xinyu

Editor, sugar maple

1

I left Hubei on January 7th. At that time, I received the order from Jingzhou, Hubei to Yiwu, Zhejiang, more than 800 kilometers, a day and a night to run. I raised my family in a sports car. I wanted to make more money. I didn't want to run an empty car. I would stop at one place, sleep in the car, wait for a new order, and then go to the next city.

I take orders on the truck help APP (similar to the truck version of Didi) , less goods and more drivers, sometimes have to snatch a single. I made another delivery from Yiwu to Guizhou, where I waited for a single day for two days and nights, then to Xiangtan, Hunan, and then back to Yiwu. Every three to five days, I would find a small town, open an hour in a small hotel room, take a shower and change clothes before leaving. After leaving Yiwu, I went to Shenzhen, 1700 kilometers, three days and three nights. I try to run as long as I can, take as short a break as I can, and sleep in the car because the truck manifest is contracted to deliver the goods within the prescribed time frame.

Everywhere I went, I would send a GPS to my family, letting them know where I was. I told them to try not to call me, because I was driving and my phone was navigating, so I would call them and they would know I was resting. During this period, we spoke on the phone. They said that there had been a respiratory system illness in Wuhan. It was very serious. Many people did not go that way. I said I was not in Wuhan. At that time, I did not know what a COVID-19 was, but I heard vaguely that. Usually I do not have time to watch the news, all day is on the road, the phone in navigation, finally arrived at the destination must take time to rest, rest and see if you can take the next job.

I waited all day in Shenzhen and pulled a load of goods to Fuzhou, Fujian Province. In Fuzhou, I was going to go home for the New Year, a boss said, a job to Sichuan, very urgent, can not find a car, can help me, give me an additional 200 yuan, I agreed. Before I left, my boss gave me a dozen masks, a can of red bull and some gloves. "You'll need them, " he said. I didn't know what I was doing.

On the way to Sichuan, a New Year has come. Arriving in Kaijiang County, Sichuan Province, on the first day of the Lunar New Year, I began to feel the impact of the license plate number beginning with "e" as I stepped off the highway. There were cops at the highway and people in Hazmat suits, and I saw that they were wearing masks, and I put mine on. They saw that I was a Hubei license plate, so they registered. I asked them what the situation was, and they said that they would now strictly control foreign vehicles.

When I arrived at my destination, I found seven or eight older men more than 20 meters away, watching my car, I do not know what the situation is. A few moments later two policemen, a man and a woman, asked about me, looked at my papers, and I kept all the highway receipts along the way, explaining to them that I was not from Hubei.

They looked into it and said it was fine, it's fine, just get out of here as soon as you can, I mean, what's going on? The police said, we are still safe in you, but now the people are more sensitive to this side of Hubei, you take care of yourself, we go as soon as you leave. I said thank you, and they left.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
During the outbreak of high-speed intersection have relevant personnel temperature chart source to see the news

I want to find a place to eat some food, the local people heard my Hubei accent, said that you are very fierce, the boss asked me if there is no problem, I told my situation, the boss is quite good, said that I am relieved. After dinner, I went back to find two small tricycles parked in front of the car, there are people taking pictures of my car, I ran to them, they said you Hubei people hurry away, do not stop here. Someone's still on the phone. I don't know if they're calling the cops or something. I told them I'd be leaving soon.

You know, I get it. During an outbreak, closed management, that's how it's supposed to be. I say okay, I leave, I leave.

Then I got on the highway, and there were all these checkpoints, and I had to take my temperature and register, but I was able to get through. I turned on my gps and looked it up. It was more than 800 kilometers from Jingzhou. I wanted to go home, but I didn't think I'd make much money on the trip. It would take me a day and a night to get home. The cost of gas and the toll was more than 1,000 yuan. I didn't want to spend so much money on an empty car to get back. I also found a source of goods on the platform, from Sichuan to Shaanxi Chenggu, I thought this is not from Hubei also a little bit closer, pull home again, I sent my car information to the owner in the past, on the highway.

About 80 kilometers away, the owner of the goods gave me a phone call, said my car in Hubei is not good, this single business is so yellow. Logistics people also told me, now national road, provincial road, rural road are set up checkpoints, high-speed down you go not far, I said this can how to do.

Since I left Fuzhou, I've only slept for over two hours. At that time, I remember that I was in Jiangyou, Sichuan Province. I wanted to get off the highway and find a place to take a bath. The staff at the checkpoint would advise me that you could get off, but the roads were blocked everywhere. Cars from other provinces were not allowed to leave, and foreign vehicles and people were forbidden to move. What's the point of going down there? The service area in Jiangyou was still parking, so I slept there for three hours, couldn't sleep, woke up, said I'd just go home, even if it cost me some money.

So I put Hubei Jingzhou into my navigation, and I drove all night, and the next morning, when it was light, I found that the service area wouldn't let me stop, so I could refuel, and no one would care, stop to rest, the service area staff hurried to let go. Did I ask why? They say that your Hubei outbreak is very serious, all from Hubei Infection, you Hubei car do not stop, do not infect us. I explained it to them everywhere, and it didn't work. Their story is, sick or not, you eat, you go, you don't stop here, that's it.

From then on, I had no place to sleep.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Master Xiao's cab cover video

2

There is no place to sleep on the highway, only a spacious place like an emergency stop, with a warning sign, where to sleep. The longest sleep lasted more than an hour. It's usually the traffic cops knocking on the windows, saying you can't park like this. It's against the law. Let's go. I said, "what if the service area doesn't allow parking? " He said, "it's the same all over the country. You'd better go back to your hometown. ".

I'm just GONNA have to move on. By the end of the night, I had a problem with my navigation. When I got to Ningqiang County in Shaanxi, he told me to get off the highway, walk up the National Highway and get back on the highway. It was one o'clock in the morning, off the highway, the staff took my temperature, register, said you can go, but vaguely told me not to go anywhere, you had better return to the highway. I said the NAV made me do it, and they didn't say anything.

I still insist on going forward, they did not specifically block, in the national road for a period of time, found everywhere blocked. The banner said no non native residents or foreign traffic, so I had to navigate back to the country road, take a detour, and then drive back to the national highway.

In the middle of the night, I am afraid of getting lost, the signal in the mountain area is not good, there is a section of road completely cut off the Internet, how can not connect up, walk for a long time before there is a signal again. A lot of the roads go around the mountains, big s over the cliff, the old ones. It's too dangerous. I have not had a rest, already a little sleepy, some mountain road and fog, visibility is only 3,4 meters, simply can not see, more than 2 meters Wide Mountain Road Ah, below is the cliff, really too terrible, too terrible. Every once in a while, I'd run into a car or two, and it was so dark, they couldn't read my license plate, so they didn't stop me.

I remember driving back to the national highway, I came across a tunnel, and soon I was able to get back on the highway. There was another checkpoint in front of the tunnel, set up a table, maybe my van was too loud, woke up the guards. He saw I was a Hubei license plate, said to hurry up, do not go I called the police. I asked him where he could go, and he pointed out the side street, which was actually kind of Nice, and he pointed me in the right direction. It goes from the bottom of the hill to the top of the hill, and from the top of the hill, it's really scary.

Between 4:30 and 5:00 a.m. , I got back on the highway.

Dawn, I still do not give up, want to see if you can find a platform to go to Hubei work, even if not to earn money. I did find one. Chenggu County to Shiyan. I contact with the owner, up said I was Hubei's car, asked her if there is no impact, the owner may not be very familiar with this situation, said you come.

When I arrived at her factory at 7 o'clock, she called again and said, "don't come here. I don't know what happened. Someone called the police. The police came to take temperature and register. Many people were watching. ". The police said that this is the case, not that we exclude you, because now the outbreak is under control, you do not pull this cargo, you go home.

I get it. I support it. No problem. Just left again. Hey. It was a little bit true, it was a little sad. There was a sentence I really wanted to say at that time. I said that the disease didn't even bring us down, but this kind of thinking of our compatriots really, really scared me. I also told them, I've been out for more than half a month, and I'm not from Hubei, I'm as healthy as you, I'm no threat to you at all, they said we also know, but it's the same all over the country, we can not let the virus spread unless we adopt this kind of closed management.

I'm back on the highway, there's still checkpoints everywhere, and you're in a small town, and people stop you and call the police. I didn't know what to do. The police told me. The highway in Hubei was closed. I said, well, I can't go home either.

I'm on the highway. I don't even know where I'm going. Home is definitely not going back, when I called home, the family said that we have many confirmed cases here, and we may not be able to return home for a while, the highways are all closed, you can not get down, the provincial roads are also closed, you go outside, see if you can find a place to settle down, get through this thing, and then come back.

Since the service area does not allow parking, I am a bit at a loss, home can not go home, the national road is closed everywhere. I don't know what to do. Navigation to Jingzhou is an ill-conceived goal. In the old days, when a destination was entered in the navigation, I would encourage myself with the remaining distance, say 1,700 kilometers, and I would tell myself, now it's four digits, running, three digits, and running, AH, two digits, as soon as you get there, use this as a way to encourage yourself and refresh yourself.

I was really at a loss. I was fined for going under 60 on the highway, but I kept going 30 or 40 and didn't know where to go. I don't think I can do this anymore. I don't think I can. It's freaking me out.

So aimlessly, I thought I'd come back closer to Jingzhou and not be ostracized, when the navigation went a little wrong, I ran the wrong way around, hadn't slept in days, and was running headlong in the opposite direction of Hanzhong. I'm really, really tired. On the 29th, I slept in a wide-open emergency parking space on the Hanzhong highway. I was tired.

At two or three o'clock in the afternoon, someone knocked on the window. I saw that it was the traffic police. They looked at my identity card and said it was illegal parking. They fined me 200 yuan. Under special circumstances, I will not deal with you for a while. I will tell them that I am too tired, can you let me sleep for a while before I go? I'm so sleepy. When they found out about it, they took me to the nearest tollbooth, and they said we could go there and fix it, you know, it's dangerous driving on the highway when you're tired. (editor's Note: It was around this time that he was caught on video of being "too tired, " which began circulating on the Internet on Feb. 8.)

At the toll booth, the clerk took my temperature, checked me in, and bought me fruit. At that time, I was really moved to tears. These days, I've been driving along. I don't know when it will end, I really can't carry it anymore. Pulling my hair out to sober myself up, I almost hit the high-speed guardrail several times, i'm so touched that someone suddenly cares so much about me and brings me food and drink. They say if you're too tired to let the provincial traffic go anywhere else, we'll find you a place to rest, and then you'll find a way back to your hometown.

Then they let me rest in the Hanzhong North Service area. Pull over here. At the beginning there must be a quarantine, observation period, they arranged me to live in the car, the morning someone gave me a temperature, also sent me steamed bread, to my car disinfection. The first day in the service area rest, I slept more than ten hours.

3

Drifting these days, I have never felt these policies unreasonable moment, I served in the military, these big right and wrong of the truth I understand, when the national crisis, every man is responsible. I can understand and support that it is a small contribution to the country to get over the difficulties.

My car is Jianghuai brand 4 meters high column Light Truck, 1 km empty fuel 7,8 cents, cargo is 1.1,1.2. From the first day to the fifth day, four days and four nights time, are empty car running, toll and gas money is a total of more than 3000 yuan, no way to save fuel, the only way is to stop, I intermittent rest time only 7,8 hours.

I started to drive a truck in October last year. My monthly income was about 6,000 yuan when I was in good condition, and a little over 5,000 yuan when I was in bad condition. The Standard Job was two days and a dozen trips a month. These days floating on the highway, half a month's income on the loss. In fact, toss about a few days, a straight line distance is only 5,600 kilometers, the cost of a few hundred dollars of gas tolls, about 1000 dollars. But in this case of non-stop running, and walk a lot of repetition of the road, invisible in the distance doubled, money spent on the oil above.

After settling down in the service area, I dared to tell my family that I was in such a mess these days. My parents were in their 70s and in poor health, so I reported good news but not bad news.

The people in the service area were nice to me, and I thought I'd try not to be a bother to anyone else so they wouldn't kick me out. In addition, in order to avoid misunderstanding, I try not to get out of the car, drink less water, about a little less crowded at night, eight or nine o'clock, I go down to eat instant noodles.

There is nothing to pass the time in the car during the day, staring blankly, sleeping. Look around, look at the sun, look at the sky, in fact, generally like we run a long time truck, this kind of loneliness can stand, also used to. The phone is a generic brand of smartphone that costs more than 400 yuan, and there are no entertainment activities inside. It's too much trouble to download an APP, and it takes up traffic.

Behind my driver's seat there is a board, 60 centimeters wide and 2 meters long, on which the bed quilt can be made to sleep. In the evening the car is too cold to start the car on the warm air blowing a blow, while charging the phone, up to 40 minutes to an hour, driving long time is also fuel consumption. There's little room in the car, so the warm air will last for a while.

Before driving the truck, I was engaged in aluminum alloy installation and production in Jiangxi. Business was not very good. In addition, the payment of wages, uh, was very troublesome, and the payment cycle was very long. I work outside the home. I'm out for a few months, and I can't take care of my family, so I quit.

I have a few friends in the sports van, they said that is a little hard, I said OK, nothing else, strength is there. I borrowed more than 20,000 yuan from some relatives and friends to buy this second-hand truck. The money hasn't been paid back yet.

Think really sorry to my son, since he was 3 years old, I have been working outside, little time with him, can only be at home with him as much as possible, play with him, let him feel a little fatherly love. The child sensible, these days video will tell me a short story, tell a joke, tell me his classmates, teachers, said their school activities.

The head of the service area has been taking this very seriously. This morning (February 8) , I was arranged in a guest room, like the hotel standard room, with air conditioning, TV and water heater can take a bath, very convenient. I can stay for free until I get home. Lying in bed feels very stretch, never so stretch to sleep. And you can roll over and feel at home.

I am homesick, Spring Festival is our traditional festival, money is no money, all want to go home for the New Year, family reunion, parents are also very worried about me. I spent the evening of the New Year's Eve in the high-speed service area, people have gone home for New Year's Eve dinner, almost no one, I only a car, also can not buy what to eat, boiled water and, or to eat instant noodles.

I really do not know when to go home, for the next thing I do not know how to plan. According to media reports today, Tianmen's Transportation Authority also contacted the head of the highway service here, saying that if I wanted to go back, they could pick me up, but I didn't want to cause them any trouble, moreover, I will also have a 14-day observation period after I return, and it will also take up the resources of my hometown. It will take a lot of twists and turns for them to come and pick me up. Originally, the local finance was not rich. Now, in the heavily affected areas, many hospitals are also in short supply, so I'm just GonNa stay here a little while longer, and I don't want to get in trouble with the government back home.

If I could go home, the first thing I would like to do is, I have a car, I could send emergency supplies to some hospitals. Since I've been out for so many days, I'm healthy and not contagious, so I'm the best person to pull the emergency supplies. We are a big agricultural city. According to past years, this should be the time for spring ploughing. Now ordinary cars can not get in. If I were a person from a non-epidemic area, it would be more appropriate for me to pull these production materials. I would like to make some contributions to my hometown.

In the first few days in the service area, I could sleep from dark to the next morning. After three or four days, I was out of balance. Sometimes I woke up suddenly. I was in a daze, sometimes I look out and I don't know if it's real or not. Doesn't even know he exists anymore. It could be that you've been in a closed environment for a long time, or that you're stressed.

We live by trucks. You see, cars in Hubei are very sensitive now. I don't know if the psychology of the people will turn around after the epidemic is over. If they still reject cars in Hubei like this, I don't know if I can still load them.

My family lives off this car. What am I GONNA do? My wife doesn't have a job, my family of five is counting on this car, if it doesn't run, it won't work. That's the hardest question of all. I can't go home. I can get over it.

My son is in the sixth grade this year. He will take the junior high school exam in September. He is in a dilemma. He doesn't know what to do about the tuition fees in the future. If you get good grades, you can go to a good school, if you don't do well, you can't go to a bad school, you can't ruin his life, but you have to find a school, spend some money, and if you don't have 20,000 or so saved by September, it's really holding him up.
